<br>
In any event, she began to randomly walk, just to see what she could find, unbeknownst to her, she was walking in the direction of Thanatos's palace. As she closed in, something walked past her, which caught her attention, seeing as it looked downright identical to the father of the family she had dispatched weeks ago. She walked deeper into his territory and her eyes widened as she saw the specticle before her of all the souls roaming free.....that wasn't right.  She crossed her arms over her chest and headed in the direction of the path leading to the door of the palace, maybe Thanatos knew what was up.... <p>{*}In the heart of man lies Eris, Goddess of Discord and Strife, dont try to deny it. {*}</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thanatosofdeath@amazonsunite>Thanatos of Death</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.joerghuber.com/images/art_c48.jpeg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(3/16/03 1:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Eris to the rescue?</span><hr size=1> *Thanatos sees Eris heading toward his tower, silent prayer for help answered. His dragon does a dive down towards Eris and lands next to her.* <br>
 <br>
"Thank Zeus your here Eris... Somehow the souls have freed themselves from there underworld bonds, I have no idea how this happened. I might hold them back long enough, while you go get help, or someone who might know more about this." <br>
 <br>
*Thanatos's eyes grew very red for a few moments, as the ground beneath them began to rumble. Suddenly things started to pop out of the ground... Armored skeletons to be exact. There were about 40 of them that began to charge into the mass of the living dead. Thanatos then jumped off his dragon.* <br>
 <br>
"Take my dragon, that it might help you, it knows its way around very well the underworld, it will get ride of any trouble along the way..." <br>
